To create a Node.js Express server that serves an HTML form and stores the submitted data in a SQLite database, follow these steps:

1. Install necessary packages

First, you need to install the required packages for your project. Run the following commands in your terminal:

```bash
mkdir express-form-demo
cd express-form-demo
npm init -y
npm install express body-parser sqlite3 ejs
```

2. Create the server file

Create a new file called `server.js` in your project folder and add the following code:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const bodyParser = require('body-parser');
const sqlite3 = require('sqlite3').verbose();
const path = require('path');

const app = express();

app.use(bodyParser.urlencoded({ extended: false }));
app.set('view engine', 'ejs');
app.set('views', path.join(__dirname, 'views'));

const db = new sqlite3.Database(':memory:', (err) => {
  if (err) {
    return console.error(err.message);
  }
  console.log('Connected to the in-memory SQlite database.');
});

db.run('CREATE TABLE users (name TEXT, color TEXT)', (err) => {
  if (err) {
    return console.error(err.message);
  }
  console.log('Created table "users"');
});

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  db.all('SELECT * FROM users', [], (err, rows) => {
    if (err) {
      throw err;
    }
    res.render('index', { users: rows });
  });
});

app.post('/submit', (req, res) => {
  const name = req.body.name;
  const color = req.body.color;

  db.run(`INSERT INTO users(name, color) VALUES(?, ?)`, [name, color], function (err) {
    if (err) {
      return console.error(err.message);
    }
    res.redirect('/');
  });
});

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server is running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

3. Create the HTML form

Create a new folder called `views` in your project folder and create a new file called `index.ejs` inside it. Add the following code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Express Form Demo</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Submit Your Name and Favorite Color</h1>
  <form action="/submit" method="post">
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
    <br>
    <label for="color">Favorite Color:</label>
    <input type="text" id="color" name="color" required>
    <br>
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
  </form>

  <h2>Previous Submissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <% users.forEach(user => { %>
      <li><%= user.name %> - <%= user.color %></li>
    <% }); %>
  </ul>
</body>
</html>
```

4. Run the server

Now you can run your server by executing the following command in your terminal:

```bash
node server.js
```

5. Test the application

Open your browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000. You should see the form where you can submit your name and favorite color. After submitting the form, you will see the list of previously submitted names and colors.

